M|references|These phrases often add nothing. Delete them:
M|references|- a total of
M|references|- absolutely
M|references|- actually
M|references|- all things being equal
M|references|- as a matter of fact
M|references|- at the end of the day
M|references|- at this moment in time
M|references|- basically
M|references|- currently (when "now" or nothing works)
M|references|- I am of the opinion that (use: I think)
M|references|- in due course (use: soon, or say when)
M|references|- in the final analysis
M|references|- it should be understood
M|references|- last but not least
M|references|- obviously
M|references|- of course
M|references|- quite
M|references|- really
M|references|- the fact of the matter is
M|references|- to all intents and purposes
